Re: Development of alert system

Bitcointalk

2010-08-24 23:51:12 UTC - [11]Original Post

   If youʼre so paranoid that youʼre getting hysterical over this, then
   surely youʼre paranoid enough that if a warning message displays on the
   status bar, youʼll check the website and forum.
   I think if another bug like the overflow bug occurs, itʼs important
   that automated websites stop trading until their admins can check out
   whatʼs going on and decide what to do.  If you decide itʼs a false
   alarm and want to take your chances, you can use the "-disablesafemode"
   switch.
